Q1. What is Docker?
-> docker is a tool which is open-source centlised platform(Developers use different OS, setups, and versions â†’ â€œit works on my machineâ€ problem âŒ , works everywhereâ†’developer, tester, production server), 
   designed to create(creates a container image from docker file) deploye(You push your image to Docker Hub Then pull and deploy it (i.e., start a container) on another machine.) & run(Docker runs the container) application.
-> docker written in 'go' language.
-> docker uses container on the host O.S to run application, it allows applications to use the same linux kernel as a system on the host computer
   rather than creating a whole Virtual O.S 

Q2. Advantage Of Docker?
-> Resolves Compatibility problem using containerization
-> No pre-allocation of RAM.
-> It is light in weight.
-> You can re-use the image.
-> Software upgrades can be done easily on multiple machines using docker
-> It took very less time to create the container

Note:
âœ” Docker Engine acts as a bridge between the container and the host OS
âœ” Containers donâ€™t have their own kernel, they use the hostâ€™s kernel
âœ” Docker Engine manages containers but does not create them â€” it runs & controls them so Docker CLI or Docker Daemon creates the container not not directly the Engine itself.

Q3. Disadvantage Of Docker?
-> Docker is not good solution for application which requires Rich GUI.
-> Difficult to manage large number of containers.
-> Docker is suitable when the development O.S and testing O.S are same , if the O.S is different we should use Virtual Machine.
-> No solutions for Data Recovery & Backup.

Q4. VIRTUALIZATION / Virtual Machine ðŸ’»     VS     CONTAINERIZATION / Container ðŸ³  :
- Virtualization poora OS duplicate karta hai, jabki Containerization sirf application aur dependencies ko isolate, Isolation means: Ek container doosre container ko disturb nahi karta, sab alag environment me run hote hain even though they share the same OS kernel.)
   karta hai OS ko share karke.
|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|1ï¸âƒ£ Virtualization (VM-based) :                                                       2ï¸âƒ£ Containerization (Docker-based):                                                 |
|      - VM ke andar kya hota hai?                                                             - Container ke andar kya hota hai?                                          |
|                        - Guest Operating System (Windows/Linux etc.)                                      - Application                                                  |
|                        - Application                                                                      - Libraries & dependencies                                     |
|                        - Libraries                                                                           (No full OS)                                                |
|                        - Dependencies                                                                                                                                    |
|      - Characteristics :                                                                      - Characteristics :                                                        |
|                        - Har VM apna complete OS chalata hai                                                - Very lightweight                                           |
|                        - Heavy size (GBs)                                                                   - Fast startup (seconds me)                                  |
|                        - Boot hone me time lagta hai                                                        - Less resource usage                                        |
|                        - Strong isolation (kaafi secure)                                                    - OS kernel host se share karta hai                          |
|                        - More resource usage (CPU/RAM high consume)                                         - Isolation VM se thoda kam, but enough for apps             |
