Q4. Explain Docker Architecture?

Docker Client  â†’  Docker Daemon  â†’  Docker Registry
        â†‘                  â†“
        â””â”€â”€â”€â”€ Containers / Images â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜

1ï¸âƒ£ Docker Client : Ye wo tool hai jisse aap Docker ko commands dete ho, jaise: docker run , docker pull, docker ps etc.. Client commands ko Docker Daemon ko send karta hai.
2ï¸âƒ£ Docker Daemon (dockerd) :  Ye Docker ka main brain hai. Daemon ye kaam karta hai: Containers run karna, Images pull/push karna, Networks create/manage karna, Volumes manage karna
                              Daemon hi sari heavy lifting karta hai, client sirf request bhejta hai.
3ï¸âƒ£ Docker Registry (Hub or Private Registry) : Yaha Docker images stored hoti hain. Default registry = Docker Hub , Daemon jab image pull karta hai, yahi se karta hai.

